@node introduction
CyberAviGui is a user interface for a AVI player called CyberAvi.
CyberAvi is on aminet gfx/show/CyberAVI.lha.
CyberAvi requires OS3.0 and AGA.
@endnode

@node requirements
CyberAviGui Requires:

-CyberAvi v1.9 or later

-OS3.0 and AGA, Actually CyberAvi requires it

-Reqtools Library V38

-Amiga would be nice ;)
@endnode

@node usage
Explanation of buttons:

SMR        -Pops up a screen mode requester

Force24    -Forces to 24bit display

Gray       -Displays grayscale

AGA        -Forces AGA

HAM8       -Displays HAM8

Loop       -Does what it says

MaxFPS     -Plays at maximum speed

NoSound    -Guess

NoVideo    -Guess again

Load       -Load Avi(s)

About      -About box

Snap       -Snapshots window position


Tooltypes:

EXE        Location of your Cyberavi executable.
Defaults to C:Cyberavi
example:   EXE=bin:cyberavi

PICTURE    a backdrop picture of your choice.
Note that the picture must be 240*141 IFF or a bit bigger
but don't make it too big. You have been warned!!
example:   PICTURE=pics:backdrop.iff
@endnode

@node bugs
Bugs:

Program crashes if the specified backdrop picture can't be found

If you have previously snapshotted the window e.g at position 320,320
and change the screenmode to smaller the window fails to open.
Just delete the file s:cybgui.pos and it works again.


IMPORTANT!!

If you find any bugs please @{"contact" link contact} me that I can fix them.
@endnode

